@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "CrewTrack Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 transition-colors">
    <!-- Header -->
    <section class="py-24 lg:py-32 border-b border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-neutral-400 dark:text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest">
                Legal — CrewTrack Android App
            </span>
            <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white leading-tight">
                CrewTrack Privacy Policy
            </h1>
            <p class="mt-6 text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400">
                Last updated: June 2026
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Content -->
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
            <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert max-w-none">

                <h2>About This Policy</h2>
                <p>
                    This policy describes how the <strong>CrewTrack</strong> Android application
                    (the "App") collects, uses, stores, and shares information when used by
                    field crews and administrators of a business client (your "Employer").
                </p>
                <p>
                    CrewTrack is developed and operated by <strong>Learned Geek LLC</strong>
                    ("we," "us," or "our"), a Wisconsin limited liability company. CrewTrack
                    is licensed to businesses (your "Employer") who deploy it to their crew
                    members for workforce management. In privacy terms, your Employer is the
                    <em>data controller</em> and Learned Geek LLC is the <em>data processor</em>
                    acting on their behalf.
                </p>
                <p>
                    For the general Learned Geek website privacy policy, see
                    <a asp-action="Privacy">/policies/privacy</a>. This document covers the
                    CrewTrack mobile app specifically.
                </p>

                <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

                <h3>Account Information</h3>
                <p>When your Employer provisions your CrewTrack account, we collect and store:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Your name (as provided by your Employer)</li>
                    <li>Your email address (used for login)</li>
                    <li>Your role (Owner, Supervisor, or Crew)</li>
                    <li>Your preferred display language (English or Spanish)</li>
                    <li>A password hash (we never store the plaintext password)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Location Data (GPS)</h3>
                <p>
                    CrewTrack collects precise GPS coordinates from your device in the
                    following situations, when authorized via Android location permissions:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>When you clock in or clock out</strong> — a single coordinate
                        is recorded with the time entry, used by your Employer to verify the
                        clock event happened at the job site.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>When you start, complete, or skip a task</strong> — a single
                        coordinate is recorded with the action, used to verify on-site work.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>While clocked in, in the background</strong> — your device
                        periodically reports its location while a foreground-service
                        notification is displayed (typically every 30 seconds when moving).
                        This is how your Employer verifies travel time between job sites
                        and confirms time billed against location. Background location
                        tracking stops the moment you clock out.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    Location data is transmitted to our servers and forwarded to your
                    Employer's administrators via the CrewTrack admin web interface. You
                    can revoke location permissions at any time via your Android Settings;
                    doing so will prevent the app from recording location during clock-in
                    events and may affect your Employer's payroll verification.
                </p>

                <h3>Photos</h3>
                <p>
                    The App allows you to capture photos for documenting completed tasks,
                    material deliveries, supplier pickups, and job-site conditions. When
                    you capture a photo through the App:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>The image is stored on our servers under your Employer's account.</li>
                    <li>The image is tagged with the task, work order, time, and (if available) GPS coordinates of capture.</li>
                    <li>Your Employer's administrators can view, download, and export captured photos.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    Photos captured through CrewTrack are owned by your Employer as part
                    of their work records. They are not used for any purpose outside the
                    direct workforce-management workflow.
                </p>

                <h3>Device Identifiers</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) Token</strong> — a token
                        generated by your device's Google Play services. We use this token
                        to deliver push notifications (e.g., admin force-login messages,
                        long-shift nudges). The token is rotated by Android periodically.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Device identifier</strong> — a stable identifier that binds
                        the App installation to your account, so your Employer's admin can
                        push session messages (e.g., force-logout for a lost device).
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Activity and Audit Logs</h3>
                <p>
                    The App and our servers record:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Login and logout events (success and failure, with reason)</li>
                    <li>Lockout events when too many failed logins occur</li>
                    <li>Time entries (clock-in / clock-out timestamps)</li>
                    <li>Task actions (start, complete, skip — with timestamp and crew member)</li>
                    <li>Photo uploads (timestamp, file size, associated task)</li>
                    <li>Administrative actions performed by your Employer (force sign-in/out, lockout cleared, etc.)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    These records are visible to your Employer's administrators via the
                    CrewTrack admin web interface.
                </p>

                <h3>Technical Information</h3>
                <p>
                    When the App communicates with our servers, standard request metadata
                    is logged for security monitoring and debugging:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>IP address of the device</li>
                    <li>Approximate timing and size of API requests</li>
                    <li>Error messages and diagnostic information when failures occur</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
                <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Authenticate your access to the App</li>
                    <li>Deliver work orders, tasks, and materials assigned to you by your Employer</li>
                    <li>Record time entries used by your Employer for payroll and billing</li>
                    <li>Provide your Employer with location verification of clock events and on-site work</li>
                    <li>Send push notifications related to your work (e.g., shift status, admin messages)</li>
                    <li>Detect and resolve technical issues with the App and our servers</li>
                    <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    We do not use your personal data for advertising, do not sell it to
                    third parties, and do not share it for marketing purposes.
                </p>

                <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
                <p>We share information only as follows:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>With your Employer</strong> — Your Employer's administrators
                        have access to all data the App collects from you in the course of
                        your work, via the CrewTrack admin web interface. This is the core
                        purpose of the product.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>With Google (Firebase Cloud Messaging)</strong> — Push
                        notification delivery is performed by Google's Firebase Cloud
                        Messaging service. We send Google a message payload and your FCM
                        token; Google delivers the notification to your device. Subject to
                        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>With Mapbox</strong> — For map display, address geocoding,
                        and snapping GPS trails to roads, we send Mapbox individual
                        coordinates and addresses. Subject to
                        <a href="https://www.mapbox.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mapbox's Privacy Policy</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Legal requirements</strong> — If required by law, regulation,
                        court order, or to protect the rights or safety of users or third parties.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Data Retention</h2>
                <p>
                    We retain your data for as long as your CrewTrack account is active
                    under your Employer's deployment. Specific retention windows:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Account credentials</strong> — retained while your account
                        is active. Deleted within 30 days of account deactivation by your
                        Employer.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Location history (background GPS)</strong> — retained for 90 days
                        by default; your Employer may configure a shorter or longer window.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Clock-event GPS, task GPS, and photos</strong> — retained
                        as part of your Employer's work records for as long as your
                        Employer retains those records, typically per payroll and tax
                        record-keeping requirements (often 4-7 years in the United States).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Audit logs</strong> — retained for the lifetime of the
                        Employer's account.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Server logs (technical)</strong> — retained for 30 days.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Your Rights</h2>
                <p>
                    Because CrewTrack data is your Employer's workforce data, requests to
                    access, correct, or delete your personal information are generally
                    handled by your Employer. You may:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Request access to the data your Employer has collected about you through CrewTrack</li>
                    <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
                    <li>Request deletion of your data (subject to your Employer's record-keeping requirements)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    Contact your Employer's CrewTrack administrator for these requests.
                    If your Employer is unable or unwilling to address your request, you
                    may contact us directly at
                    <a href="mailto:hello@learnedgeek.com">hello@learnedgeek.com</a> and
                    we will work with your Employer to honor it where legally required.
                </p>

                <h2>Security</h2>
                <p>
                    We use industry-standard security measures including:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>HTTPS encryption for all data transmitted between the App and our servers</li>
                    <li>Encrypted password storage (bcrypt or equivalent hashing)</li>
                    <li>Encrypted-at-rest storage for sensitive configuration values</li>
                    <li>JWT-based authentication with short-lived access tokens (15 minutes default)</li>
                    <li>Account lockout after repeated failed login attempts</li>
                    <li>Audit logging of all administrative actions</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    However, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of
                    electronic storage is 100% secure.
                </p>

                <h2>Children</h2>
                <p>
                    CrewTrack is designed for use by adult workforce members and is not
                    intended for use by children under 18. We do not knowingly collect
                    personal information from children.
                </p>

                <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
                <p>
                    We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Material changes
                    will be communicated via the App or by email to your Employer's
                    administrator. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page
                    reflects the most recent revision.
                </p>

                <h2>Contact Us</h2>
                <p>
                    If you have questions about this policy or how CrewTrack handles your
                    data, please contact us at:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Learned Geek LLC</strong><br />
                    Email: <a href="mailto:hello@learnedgeek.com">hello@learnedgeek.com</a><br />
                    Website: <a href="https://learnedgeek.com">https://learnedgeek.com</a>
                </p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
